HEADWORD: Pungency
<hw>Pun"gen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being pungent or piercing; keenness; sharpness; piquancy;
<as>as, the <ex>pungency</ex> of ammonia</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>pungency</xex> of menaces.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pungent</ent>⟦br⟧
